Step 5: Questions about the data¶

What stations experience the most rainfall?¶

In [27]:
ax = df.groupby('Station')['Rain'].mean() \
    .sort_values(ascending=False).head(10) \
    .plot(kind='bar',
          title='Top 10 Stations by Average Rainfall')
ax.set_ylabel('Rainfall (mm)')
plt.show()

Has the amount of sun or rainfall changed over the years (e.g. due to climate change)?¶

In [28]:
ax = sns.regplot(data=df,
                 x='Year',
                 y='Sun',
                 scatter_kws={'s':3},
                 line_kws={'color':'blue'})
ax.set_ylabel('Sun Duration (hours)')
print("Correlation coefficient between Year and Sun Duration: ", df['Year'].dropna().corr(df['Sun'].dropna()))

Correlation coefficient between Year and Sun Duration:  0.03393592868742296
In [29]:
ax = sns.regplot(data=df,
                 x='Year',
                 y='Rain',
                 scatter_kws={'s':3},
                 line_kws={'color':'blue'})
ax.set_title('Year vs Rainfall')
ax.set_ylabel('Rainfall (mm)')
print("Correlation coefficient between Year and Rainfall: ", df['Year'].dropna().corr(df['Rain'].dropna()))

Correlation coefficient between Year and Rainfall:  0.06157350053349003
